'''Auto-Latex Equations''' is a [[Google Docs]] add-on that allows any Google Docs user to type mathematical equations inside their documents. Auto-Latex Equations uses [[MathJax]] and [[LaTeX]]-style syntax and functions similar to the [[Art of Problem Solving]] math typesetting. It can be downloaded from the Google Docs Add-on Store for free [https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/auto-latex-equations/iaainhiejkciadlhlodaajgbffkebdog here].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Auto-Latex Equations|url = http://autolatex.com/home|website = autolatex.com|access-date = 2016-01-29}}</ref>

The first version of Auto-Latex Equations was released in 2015. The original programmer, designer, and marketer of Auto-Latex Equations is Aayush Gupta, a student in the [[Bay Area]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = About Us - Auto-Latex Equations|url = https://sites.google.com/site/autolatexequations/website-builder|website = sites.google.com|access-date = 2016-01-29}}</ref>

==Users==
Auto-Latex Equations is used by teachers, professors, and students worldwide. Due to its free status and integration with Google Docs, it has become a standard in school districts worldwide. <ref>{{Cite video|title = LaTeX and Google Docs|url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Oe1BgB1LkDg|website = youtube.com|access-date = 2018-02-01}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title = Specialized Add-ons For Google Docs|url = http://www.freetech4teachers.com/2017/10/specialized-add-ons-for-google-docs.html|website = freetech4teachers.com|access-date = 2018-02-01}}</ref>


