{{Other people|Edward Arnold|Edward Arnold (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox publisher | image = | parent = | status = Defunct | founded = 1890 | founder = Edward Augustus Arnold | successor = [[Taylor & Francis]] | country = [[United Kingdom]] | headquarters = [[London]] | distribution = | keypeople = | publications = [[Book]]s, journals | topics = medicine and nursing | genre = | imprints = | revenue = | numemployees = | nasdaq = | url = }}
'''Edward Arnold Publishers Ltd''' was a [[United Kingdom|British]] publishing house with its head office in [[London]]. The firm had published books for over 100 years. It became part of the [[Hodder Education]] group in 2001.<ref>[http://www.hoddereducation.co.uk/ Hodder Education Website]</ref> In 2006, Hodder Arnold sold its academic journals to [[SAGE Publications]].<ref>{{Cite web| title = SAGE Publications Acquires Hodder Arnold's Journals| accessdate = 2018-01-27| url = http://liblicense.crl.edu/ListArchives/0606/msg00126.html}}</ref> In 2012, Hodder Education sold its medical and higher education lines, including Arnold, to [[Taylor & Francis]].<ref>[http://www.trilliumpartners.co.uk/trillium-partners-advises-hachette-uk-on-the-sale-of-its-health-sciences-and-higher-education-portfolios-to-taylor-francis-group/ Trillium Partners extends its educational and academic publishing M&A sector experience]</ref> Edward Arnold published books and journals for students, academics and professionals.
==Founder== Edward Augustus Arnold was born in [[Truro]] on 15 July 1857. His grandfather was [[Thomas Arnold]] and his uncle [[Matthew Arnold]]. He was educated at [[Eton College|Eton]] and [[Hertford College, Oxford]]. He set up his own publishing business in January 1890. He died at [[Budleigh Salterton]] on 6 November 1942.<ref>Bryan Bennett, ‘Arnold, Edward Augustus (1857–1942)’, Oxford Dictionary of National Biography, Oxford University Press, 2004; online edn, May 2008 [http://www.oxforddnb.com/view/article/47453, accessed 19 Jan 2014]</ref>
