{{About|the model|the writer|Jessica Hart}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}} {{Infobox model | name = Jessica Hart | image = Jessica Hart - 2011 Australian Grand Prix.jpg | image_size = 200 | caption = Hart at the [[2011 Australian Grand Prix]] | alt = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1986|3|26|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Sydney]], New South Wales, Australia<ref name=AMA/> | height = {{height|m=1.76}}<ref name=JHFMD>{{cite web|url=http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/Jessica_Hart |title=Jessica Hart |accessdate=12 November 2011|publisher=Fashion Model Directory|work=[[Fashion Model Directory]]}}</ref> | haircolor = Naturally dark brown | eyecolor = Blue/green | agency = {{Plainlist| * [[The Lions (agency)|The Lions]] (New York, Los Angeles) * Oui Management (Paris) * Monster Management (Milan) * [[Select Model Management]] (London) * Traffic Models (Barcelona) * UNIQUE DENMARK (Copenhagen) * Chadwick Models (Sydney)<ref>https://models.com/models/jessica-hart</ref> }} }}
'''Jessica Hart''' (born 26 March 1986) is an Australian model who appeared in the 2009 ''[[Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Issue]]''. She was born in Sydney, Australia.<ref name=AMA>{{cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/fashion/a-model-aussie/2007/07/30/1185647812228.html|title=A model Aussie|accessdate=5 February 2009|date=31 July 2007|publisher=Fairfax Digital|work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]}}</ref> She was discovered in Melbourne and has appeared on the cover of Australian ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]''.<ref name=GiGaHSfJH>{{cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0,,24144965-5012974,00.html|archive-url=https://archive.is/20121230124229/http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0,,24144965-5012974,00.html|dead-url=yes|archive-date=30 December 2012|title=Gap in Guess and Harris Scarfe for Jessica Hart|accessdate=5 February 2009|date=8 August 2008|publisher=[[The Herald and Weekly Times Ltd]]|work=[[Herald Sun]]}} </ref>
==Early life and discovery== Hart attended [[Sophia Mundi Steiner School]] in Abbotsford, Victoria until she was noticed at the age of 15 at a local shopping centre.<ref name=MH/><ref name=JtHfe>{{cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0,,23938670-27258,00.html|title=Jess takes Hart from exposure|accessdate=5 February 2009|date=29 June 2008|publisher=[[The Herald and Weekly Times Ltd]]|work=[[Herald Sun]] | first=Fiona | last=Byrne}}</ref> Another story of her rise to fame has her encouraged by an aunt to enter a modeling competition hosted by ''[[Dolly Magazine]]'' in 2000.<ref name=AMA/><ref name=GiGaHSfJH/> She won the competition with her mother, Rae, and sister, Ashley, as witnesses at [[Crown Melbourne|Crown Casino]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/dailytelegraph/gallery/0,22056,5032737-5010141,00.html|title=Gallery: Jessica Hart|accessdate=5 February 2009|publisher=News Limited|work=[[The Daily Telegraph (Sydney)|The Daily Telegraph]]}}</ref> She is known for a [[gap-tooth]] smile.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theage.com.au/news/fashion/out-with-the-pout/2007/08/30/1188067271181.html?page=fullpage#contentSwap1|title=Out with the pout|accessdate=5 February 2009|date=1 September 2007|publisher=The Age Company Ltd.|work=[[The Age]] | location=Melbourne}}</ref> Her sister, Ashley Hart, is also a model.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/ashley_hart+%28i%29/|title=Ashley Hart (I) - Fashion Model|access-date=2015-12-28|website=FashionModelDirectory.com}}</ref>
==Career== Hart moved to [[New York City]] to pursue a career in modeling and has appeared in campaigns for [[Guess (clothing)|Guess]], [[Triumph International|Triumph]] and [[Esprit Holdings|Esprit]].<ref name=MH>{{cite web|url=http://thebigchair.com.au/news/water-cooler/model-hunter|title=Model hunter|accessdate=5 February 2009|date=29 February 2008|publisher=Fairfax Digital|work=[[The Age]]|author=Lewis, Felicity}}</ref> Hart shot her Swimsuit Issue photos in Mexico in November 2008.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0,,24831532-5012974,00.html|title=Jessica Hart given Elle of a lift|accessdate=5 February 2009|date=22 December 2008|publisher=[[The Herald and Weekly Times Ltd]]|work=[[Herald Sun]]}}</ref>
