{{Orphan|date=February 2009}}
A '''pneumatic larynx''' is a device that is used to help a person talk after a [[laryngectomy]]. It uses air to produce a [[humming]] sound, which is converted to speech by movement of the [[lip]]s, [[tongue]], and [[Velum (anatomy)|velum]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.limcosolutions.com/Questions/Questions.htm|title=Tokyo Artificial Larynx Questions|website=www.limcosolutions.com|access-date=2017-05-08}}</ref>

