{{Infobox Organization |name = Scottish Childminding Association |image = |image_border = |size = |caption = |map = |msize = |mcaption = |abbreviation = SCMA |motto = Quality childminding… building confident children within a family childcare experience |formation = |extinction = |type = |status = charity and membership organisation |purpose = |headquarters = [[Stirling]] |location = |region_served= [[Scotland]] |membership = |language = English |leader_title = Chief Executive|leader_name = Maggie Simpson<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.cardonald.ac.uk/news/537_improving-training-standards-for-childminders-in-scotland|title=Improving training standards for childminders in Scotland|publisher= [[Cardonald College]], Glasgow|date= 22 November 2011|accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref> |main_organ = ''Childminding'' magazine (quarterly) |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website ={{URL|http://www.childminding.org/}} |remarks = }}
The '''Scottish Childminding Association''' (SCMA) is a [[Charitable organization|charity]] and membership organisation based in [[Stirling, Scotland]]. It provides support, training and information to childminders in [[Scotland]]. SCMA's Convenor is Barbara Anne Dennistoun and its Chief Executive is Maggie Simpson.<ref name="Staff">{{cite web | url=http://www.childminding.org/contact-us/staff-contacts | title=Staff contacts | publisher=Scottish Childminding Association | accessdate=22 March 2013}}</ref>
==Registration== By law, childminding services in Scotland must be registered with the [[Care Inspectorate (Scotland)|Care Inspectorate]], [http://www.scswis.com/index.php] the independent regulator of social care and social work services across Scotland. The Care Inspectorate regulates childminding services according to the Public Services Reform (Scotland) Act 2010 and assesses their quality to make sure they meet the [[National Care Standards (Scotland)|National Care Standards]] which are published by the [[Scottish Government]].<ref name="Registering">{{cite book | title=Registering and running a childminding service: what you need to know | publisher=[[Care Inspectorate (Scotland)|Care Inspectorate]] | year=2012 | location=Dundee}}</ref>
==Community Childminding== SCMA’s Community Childminding Service provides short-term childcare for families in need. Community Childminding Services currently operate in Aberdeen, Dumfries and Galloway, Fife, Glasgow, West Lothian and the Scottish Borders.
==Communications== The Association publishes a quarterly magazine, ''Childminding'' magazine,<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.childminding.org/about-us/childminding-magazine|title= ''Childminding'' magazine|publisher= Scottish Childminding Association|accessdate= 25 February 2012|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120102210229/http://www.childminding.org/about-us/childminding-magazine|archivedate= 2 January 2012|df= }}</ref> and operates a [[helpline]].<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.childminding.org/about-us/helpline|title= Helpline|publisher= Scottish Childminding Association|accessdate= 25 February 2012|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120323125840/http://www.childminding.org/about-us/helpline|archivedate= 23 March 2012|df= }}</ref>
